The paper deals with image segmentation, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves training an inference network to approximate the posterior distribution of latent variables, which is a machine learning technique (cs.LG). The use of latent variables is also a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of classifiers and prior work on localization cues, which are topics in natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the VOC 2012 dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset in multimedia (cs.MM).
